# Host Caddy snippet for MrList. Caddy terminates TLS (auto Let's Encrypt) and
# proxies to the app container's published port (APP_PORT in .env).
#
# HTTP/3 is disabled on purpose: after the first response advertises `Alt-Svc:
# h3`, iOS switches to QUIC (UDP/443), and iOS Shortcuts' POST over QUIC fails
# with "The network connection was lost" on networks where QUIC is flaky/blocked
# (Safari falls back to h2, Shortcuts doesn't). Keeping clients on h1/h2 fixes the
# Siri webhook. Caddy still sets X-Forwarded-* so Better Auth marks cookies Secure.

{
	servers {
		protocols h1 h2
	}
}

mrlist.torpasweb.com {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy localhost:3002
}
